3. Functional Requirements
3.1 Vehicle Tracking Requirements
REQ-001: Real-Time Vehicle Location Display
Description: The system shall display current GPS locations of all fleet vehicles in real-time. Priority: High Source: Fleet Manager requirement for live vehicle visibility
Inputs:
â€¢	Motive API vehicle location data
â€¢	GPS coordinates (latitude, longitude)
â€¢	Vehicle identification information
Processing:
â€¢	Parse API responses from multiple Motive endpoints
â€¢	Handle coordinate format variations (lat/lng vs lat/lon)
â€¢	Validate coordinate ranges and data quality
â€¢	Update display every 60 seconds automatically
Outputs:
â€¢	Vehicle location table with GPS coordinates
â€¢	Vehicle status indicators (Moving, Idle, Stationary, Offline)
â€¢	Current speed and direction information
â€¢	Last update timestamps in Eastern Time
Error Handling:
â€¢	Graceful degradation when API is unavailable
â€¢	Display cached data when real-time data fails
â€¢	Clear error messages for invalid coordinates
REQ-002: Vehicle Status Classification
Description: The system shall automatically classify vehicle status based on GPS and speed data. Priority: High
Status Categories:
â€¢	Moving: Speed > 5 mph for 2+ consecutive minutes
â€¢	Idle: Speed 1-5 mph (loading/unloading activities)
â€¢	Stationary: Speed = 0 mph for 5+ consecutive minutes
â€¢	Offline: No GPS data received for 10+ minutes
Processing Logic:
â€¢	Implement state machine for status transitions
â€¢	Apply hysteresis to prevent rapid status changes
â€¢	Consider speed trends over time windows
